29/04/2004
LONDON, United Kingdom -- Romania sent shockwaves across the football world when it upset Germany 5-1 on a busy night of Euro 2004 warm-up matches Wednesday (28 April). It was Germany's worst defeat since losing to England 5-1 three years ago. In other football action, Slovenia lost to Switzerland 1-2 in Berne, while Ivica Klasnic scored his first international goal as Croatia beat Macedonia 1-0. The Netherlands defeated Greece 4-0 at home, while Bulgaria defeated Cameroon 3-0 in Sofia. Serbia-Montenegro ended its run of seven consecutive defeats, holding Northern Ireland to a 1-1 draw in Belfast. Albania drew 1-1 against Estonia in Tallinn. Turkey beat Belgium in Brussels 3-2. (BBC, AFP - 28/04/04)
